				<div id="body-content" style="position: relative;">
															<h1>Resource Centre &amp; Lending Library</h1>																									<div id="node-113" class="node">



  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <span class="print-link"><span class="print_html"><a href="http://www.sbhao.on.ca/print/programs-services/care-and-support/resource-centre" title="Display a printer-friendly version of this page." class="print-page" onclick="window.open(this.href); return false" rel="nofollow"><img src="/sites/default/modules/print/icons/print_icon.gif" alt="Print Page" title="Print Page" width="16" height="16" class="print-icon print-icon-margin" />Print Page</a></span><span class="print_mail"><a href="http://www.sbhao.on.ca/printmail/113" title="Send this page by email." class="print-mail" rel="nofollow"><img src="/sites/default/modules/print/icons/mail_icon.gif" alt="Send by email" title="Send by email" width="16" height="16" class="print-icon print-icon-margin" />Send by email</a></span></span><p>The SB&amp;H Resource Centre provides extensive up-to-date information on spina bifida, hydrocephalus and disability-related topics. We also provide and distribute unique materials such as booklets, kits, videos, and customized information packages.</p>
<p><strong>Where are we?</strong> The Resource Centre &amp; Lending Library is located in the SB&amp;H offices, Suite #1006 (10th Floor) at 555 Richmond Street West, 1 block east of Bathurst Street.</p>
<p><strong>Who can access our centre?</strong> The Resource Centre is accessible to individuals with spina bifida and/or hydrocephalus, their families, educators, health care professionals, students and all other interested persons.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<h3>
	How to Reach Us</h3>
<p>The Resource Centre &amp; Lending Library is open to the public, 9am til 5pm daily, Monday thru Friday. Our services can be accessed:</p>
<p>in Person: Suite #1006, 555 Richmond Street West, Toronto<br />
	by eMail: <a href="mailto:provincial@sbhao.on.ca">provincial@sbhao.on.ca</a><br />
	by Phone: 416-214-1056 or 800-387-1575<br />
	by Fax: 416-214-1446<br />
	by Mail: 555 Richmond St.W, P.O.Box 103, Ste.1006, Toronto, ON M5V 3B1</p>
<p>
	Detailed descriptions of all materials available on request.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<h3>
	Lending Library</h3>
<p>What&#39;s Available? The Resource Centre Lending Library includes: (Select a topic to view detailed listings)</p>
<ul>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/Books-2012.pdf" target="_blank">Books</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/Newsletters-2012.pdf" target="_blank">Newsletters</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/CD-Roms-2012.pdf" target="_blank">CDRoms</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/Journals-2012.pdf" target="_blank">Journals</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/DVDs-2012.pdf" target="_blank">DVDs</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/Assistive%20Device%20Catalogues.pdf" target="_blank">Assistive Device Catalogues</a></li>
<li>
		<a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/Library%20Listings/VHS%20Videos-2012.pdf" target="_blank">Video Tapes</a></li>
</ul>
<p>Resource materials are available on loan from SB&amp;H. All library items can be borrowed for a three-week period, free-of-charge, and will be mailed to you.&nbsp;You are responsible for returning the items on their due date. A replacement fee will be charge for any items not returned.<br />
	&nbsp;</p>
<h3>
	Information Packages</h3>
<p>The SB&amp;H Resource Centre has hundreds of fact sheets and articles available on spina bifida and hydrocephalus, as well as many other disability-related topics. Each information package is made-to-order, and if we don&#39;t have the information or material requested we will do our best to locate it for you.</p>
<p>PRE-PACKAGED INFORMATION is available on the following topics:</p>
<ul>
<li>
		Hydrocephalus</li>
<li>
		Spina Bifida</li>
<li>
		Spina Bifida Occulta</li>
<li>
		Parent Information</li>
<li>
		Adult Information</li>
<li>
		Youth Information</li>
<li>
		Student Information</li>
<li>
		Folic Acid</li>
<li>
		Latex Allergy</li>
</ul>
<p>CUSTOMIZED PACKAGES are also available on these or any other related topic:</p>
<ul>
<li>
		Tethered Cord Syndrome</li>
<li>
		Arnold Chiari Malformation</li>
<li>
		Education</li>
<li>
		Lifestyle</li>
<li>
		Recreation</li>
<li>
		Sexuality</li>
<li>
		Accessibility</li>
<li>
		Assistive Devices</li>
<li>
		Financial Assistance</li>
</ul>
<h3>
	<br />
	Resources to Own</h3>
<p>SB&amp;H is the only organization in the province addressing the particular needs of individuals with spina bifida and/or hydrocephalus (sbh)&nbsp;and their families. We develop, produce, sell and maintain an inventory of educational and informational materials related to spina bifida and hydrocephalus. We feel it essential that those with sbh as well as family, extended family, friends and health &amp; education professionals be aware and informed of these conditions.</p>
<p>	Download and print the <a href="/sites/default/files/file/documents/publications%20brochure-2012-FINAL-web.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>PUBLICATIONS LIST ORDER FORM</strong></a> to place your order.</p>
<h2 class="rteindent1">
	<strong>NEW!!!!</strong>&nbsp;The latest edition of the SB&amp;H <a href="http://www.sbhao.on.ca/programs-services/resource-centre/-guide-hydrocephalus">A Guide to Hydrocephalus/Le guide de l&#39;hydrocephalie</a>, is now available from the Association!</h2>
<p>For more information please call 416-214-1056 or email <a href="mailto:provincial@sbhao.on.ca?subject=Library%20%26%20Resource%20Centre">provincial@sbhao.on.ca</a></p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
  </div>

